Money Stuff =0A I think a lot about what I sometimes call =E2=80=9Cabstract=
 commodity space.=E2=80=9D =0ASometimes you want to buy nickel or aluminum =
or coffee or cocoa to mak =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/cl=
ick=3Fs=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12609388&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233b=
e620525&p=3D02132025>=0A=0A=0A=0AGold vaults=0A=0AI think a lot about what =
I sometimes call =E2=80=9Cabstract commodity space.=E2=80=9D =0ASometimes y=
ou want to buynickel <> or aluminum <> or coffee <> or cocoa <> to =0Amake =
batteries or beer cans or cappuccino or chocolate bars, so you go to some =
=0Asupplier and negotiate a contract for the delivery of a useful amount of=
 a =0Aparticular grade of the commodity to your factory. Sometimes, though,=
 you want =0Ato bet on the price of nickel or aluminum or coffee or cocoa, =
to hedge some =0Arisk to your business or just as a speculative bet. So you=
 buy commodityfutures=0A, financial assets that reflect the price of a comm=
odity but don=E2=80=99t require you =0Ato store it or worry about it spoili=
ng.=0A=0AThe way these futures often work is that there are big warehouses =
